  ${
    $d x y z w A $.  $( ` x y z w ` are dummy. $)
    zfun2.1 $e |- A e. V $.
    $( The ZF Axiom of Union in class notation.   This says that if ` A ` is
       a set i.e. ` A e. V ` , then the union of ` A ` is also a set.
       Same as Axiom 3 of [TakeutiZaring] p. 16. $)
    zfun2   $p |- U. A e. V $=
      ( vz vx vy cv cuni cvv wcel wceq unieq eleq1d wex wel wb wal wi wa axun
