  ${
    $d x A $.  $( ` x ` is dummy. $)
    $( The ZF Axiom of Union in class notation, in the form of a theorem
       instead of an inference.  We use the antecedent ` A e. B ` instead of
       ` A e. V ` to make the theorem more general and thus shorten some
       proofs; obviously ` V ` is one possibility for ` B ` . $)
    zfun2g   $p |- ( A e. B -> U. A e. V ) $=
      ( vx cv cuni cvv wcel wceq unieq eleq1d visset zfun2 vtoclg ) CDZEZFGAEZF
      GCABNAHOPFNAIJNCKLM $.
